Paper: hep-th/9305002

Date: 1993-05-03

Title: Quantum Mechanical Interaction-Free Measurements

Authors: Avshalom C. Elitzur and Lev Vaidman

Comments: (revised file with no need for macro), 12, TAUP 1865-91#

A novel manifestation of nonlocality of quantum mechanics is presented. It isshown that it is possible to ascertain the existence of an object in a givenregion of space without interacting with it. The method might have practicalapplications for delicate quantum experiments.